        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12777",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Related to this issue there are three major problems...\n\n1.) The user needs a list of messages, probably an array or an file, where he can find all messages which he needs to translate. And this is relevant for all classes of the framework.\n\n2.) Related the \"translatable\" messages we also have the problem that exceptions have none parameters or one or two or even three which also have to be returned or even more...\n\n3.) The messages also have to be viewable if Zend Translate is not avaiable because the user works only with some classes and deleted the rest.\n\nGreetings\nThomas, Zend_Translate-Master :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-15T13:31:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-15T13:31:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12781",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree.   For example, we would need to replace the variable portions out of the message strings with place holders and bundle the values of the placeholders as lists with each message returned.\n\nAlso, we should carefully distinguish between error messages intended for the developer of the ZF app, and error messages that are intended for reading by the users of the ZF app. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
